ese behaviors not only harm others but also disrupt the individual's ability to integrate socially and academically. The disorder is marked by a pattern of actions that are often severe and persistent, requiring intervention to address the underlying issues and mitigate their impact on the individual and society.\",7\r\n338,KRAEPELIN,\"Kraepelin was a prominent German psychiatrist who made significant contributions to the field of mental health through his classification of mental illnesses. He advanced the understanding of psychiatric disorders by focusing on clinical observations and etiology, which laid the groundwork for modern psychiatric diagnoses. Kraepelin is particularly known for his classification of non-organic mental disorders into distinct categories, including schizophrenia, manic-depressive psychosis (now known as bipolar disorder), and paranoia. His work has had a lasting influence on the field of psychiatry, shaping the way mental illnesses are diagnosed and treated today.\",6\r\n2339,THALAMUS,\"The thalamus is a brain region involved in sensory and motor signal relay, and its anterior part has been studied in relation to aggressive and sexual behaviors in animals.\",2\r\n344,MODERN PSYCHIATRY,\"Modern psychiatry began in the 19th century with the work of Griesinger and Kraepelin, focusing on brain disorders and clinical classification\",2\r\n1168,RITANSERIN,Ritanserin is a 5-HT 2 antagonist that can improve negative and affective symptoms of schizophrenia but not positive symptoms,1\r\n1173,MIDBRAIN TEGMENTUM,The midbrain tegmentum is the origin of 5-HT neurons that project to various brain regions,1\r\n1174,RAPHE NUCLEI,The raphe nuclei are the origin of 5-HT neurons that project to various brain regions,1\r\n1175,CORTEX,The cortex is a brain region where 5-HT neurons project and play a role in schizophrenia,1\r\n2338,MEDNICK,\"Mednick is a researcher who conducted comparative studies showing that adolescents with antisocial behavior exhibit low 